5. Warn against common mistakes

## Quality Standards

**Do:**
- Cite specific episodes/guests
- Provide concrete frameworks
- Give actionable next steps
- Show multiple perspectives
- Be tactical and specific

**Don't:**
- Make up quotes or episodes
- Give generic PM advice not from transcripts
- Over-rely on one guest's perspective
- Provide advice outside transcript coverage
- Be vague or theoretical

## Technical Notes

- Transcripts are 25k+ tokens each (large!)
- Use Grep first to find relevant episodes
- Read frontmatter (first 15 lines) to check relevance
- Read full transcript only when needed
- Use context lines (-C flag) for quotes with context

